1. Run debug from VS Code

Sup?  So I am trying to debug files in Typescript and I am ok, but I am having difficulty setting a breakpoint on a file that is inside a folder.  However, if I step into the function from `main.ts`, it shows the file with the message "read-only inlined content from source map".  I would like to figure out what I did wrong or if it is not supported to be able to go to a lower file directly yet.  

